current_evidence:
  - frames/t5b-pentagon-handoff-activation-smoke.evaluation.log records closed_watchdog_assisted and autonomous_closure false.
  - frames/t5c-recipient-self-watchdog-smoke.evaluation.log records goal.incomplete because Maya did not produce WATCHDOG_ACK or WATCHDOG_NO_HANDOFF after Theo's handoff.
  - frames/pentagon-purpose-repair-2026-05-22.log records that MCP send_message produced 0/9 PURPOSE_PATCHED, 0/9 PURPOSE_BLOCKED, 9/9 SILENT before exact-DM UI activation.
  - frames/pentagon-model-refresh-2026-05-22.log records the latest default-model drift and repair.
  - Direct MCP tools/list at 2026-05-22T21:57Z exposed send_message, find_conversation, read_messages, caller-scoped schedule_action, and spawn_agent, but no trigger_turn, target_agent_id, executeAgentTurn, or target conversation scheduling primitive.
  - MCP spawn_agent created T5d Activation Engineer and send_message delivered the T5d prompt, but no local codex exec worker process appeared and read_messages showed only Priya's spawn/message entries after the observation window.
  - A negative probe passed hidden agent_id, target_agent_id, and conversation_id fields to schedule_action. The tool accepted the request and returned action 0162deda-7227-47f4-bb66-4b44023acc1e, but list_scheduled_actions showed no target metadata. After the cron window the action was no longer pending, yet the T5d conversation still contained only Priya's spawn/message entries, T5d current_task was null, and no codex exec worker process appeared.
  - A later readback of the Theo-Maya conversation found delayed T5c ACKs from Maya at 2026-05-22T20:50:57Z and 2026-05-22T20:53:08Z. These invalidate a permanent "no ACK ever" claim, but not the autonomy blocker because they landed far outside the intended watchdog window.
  - After live UI selection/heartbeat catch-up, Pentagon spawned multiple local codex exec workers. Token-to-agent mapping showed MCP-attributed workers running gpt-5.5 for Maya, Theo, Priya, Rowan, Quinn, Avery, Sam, Ravi, Casey, Simone, Sofia, and Carmen.
  - Theo's live token sent a fresh T5d hash to Maya at 2026-05-22T22:06:08Z. After a 90 second observation window, the Theo-Maya conversation still had no MAYA_T5D_ACK or MAYA_T5D_BLOCKED response for T5D_HEARTBEAT_HANDOFF_2026-05-22T2208Z.

verdict: blocked
reason: >
  The current Pentagon surface proves direct UI activation and watchdog-assisted
  delivery, but not fully autonomous peer handoff activation. A target-agent
  turn primitive, or an equivalent scheduled action with explicit target
  routing and visible target-thread output, is required before easy/medium/hard/
  extra-hard autonomy can be claimed. spawn_agent plus send_message creates an
  agent/conversation and context, but did not prove autonomous execution in the
  live observation window. Hidden target fields on schedule_action also did not
  prove target execution; the public MCP wrapper remains caller-scoped in
  practice. Heartbeat catch-up can eventually start agents, but current evidence
  does not prove bounded Theo-to-Maya activation after a new handoff.
